description: We are pleased to offer this 1968 Mustang Custom. This is truly an absolutely beautiful resto-mod that was rotisserie frame off restored and assembled with meticulous care and attention to detail.  It has only approximately 1,000 miles on it since the restoration so it is still very fresh and new.  The show quality Cadillac Escalade Pearl White three stage paint shines perfectly. While it was on the rotisserie, the frame was powder blasted to get rid of any possible rust spots and antirust Rhino Lining material was sprayed all inside and underside of the car. The engine compartment was fabricated and shock towers removed to accept the rebuilt 1975 Chrylser big block 440 cubic inch V8.   A Mustang II power rack and pinion with outside coil over springs and shocks were added. The carburetor is a 650 Edelbrock sitting on an Edelbrock aluminum intake manifold and has a medium Thumper Cam. The transmission tunnel was altered to accept the Chrysler 727 automatic transmission and was rebuilt at the same time as the motor. The headers are international chrome. The heads were shaved and heavy duty valves and springs and a new crank was installed. The ignition is a high output electronic MSD ignition system. The rear end is a Ford 308 limited slip and was rebuilt with new hubs and bearings and has traction bars and heavy duty leaf springs. A new complete wiring harness was installed to make sure there were no bugs in the electrical system. It has 4-wheel power disc brakes and the front end is a new Probuilt full rack and pinion suspension with power steering. The exhaust is stainless steel Flow Master dual pipe system. The car has new doors, new glass, new floors, new dash and cluster, new hood, new truck lid, new gas tank, new blacked out chrome all the way around, new front and rear glass, a Flaming River stainless steel tilt steering column and has a new headliner with pad. A sound deadener was installed on the inside floor of the car before the carpets were installed. This car can cruise very nicely on the highway at 2100 RPM at 65 MPH. The black leather interior adds the luxury touch. It has new tires with Mustang Cobra wheels. You won’t find another Mustang like this.  All receipts and documentation is included.  The car is ready for cruising and going to car shows to win many awards! We can coordinate shipping anywhere. Please contact Savannah Classic Cars at 912-235-2347.
title: 1968 Ford Mustang

description: This is the classic pony car with a very different attitude.  The 1986 Ford Mustang SVO took an American muscle icon and added a dose of energy pumping turbo power for a rare package that will make you realize this is a rare value-priced sleeper.

We all wanted more power in the '80s but we weren't sure if some regulations were going to outlaw our favorite cars.  Ford decided one way to approach these unsure times was with a traditional V8, and cool limited edition turbo car that was lighter but made the same power.  The guys at Ford's Special Vehicle Operations (SVO) developed this limited edition coupe that carried the Mustang's fastback style, but with some very distinctive touches.  It's instantly recognizable as a special car with features like a unique front end, offset hood scoop for the turbo's ram air, and dual rear spoilers.  All of these unique elements are present today on this fastback, and they look great against the factory-correct 2A Bright Red paint.  When these special SVO cars were new, they were about double the price of the base Mustang LX, and so you can understand that this is a rare model with only 3,382 produced in 1986.

Just like the exterior, the interior shares many premium Mustang GT elements, but has enough unique pieces for the SVO to be all its own.  It starts with the exclusive sport bucket seats with added adjustable supports, a cool SVO three-spoke steering wheel, and a Hurst short throw shifter.  Because this came at a premium price, it also came loaded with features.  This includes power windows, power locks, electric rear defrost, digital clock, and provisions for air conditioning.  There's even a newer AM/FM/CD stereo with auxiliary input to play all of your modern tunes.  It's a true driver's car.  That's why you get the full gauge pack, including large tach to make sure you can see when this turbo motor really catches its breath.

The advantage of getting a car from the SVO team meant it was built by engineers who wanted to make the best performance machine around.  That's why this special Mustang is much more than just bolting on a turbo.  We believe the 2.3-liter turbocharged, and intercooled, four-cylinder engine is original, and we know it's both smart and tough. This is a computer-controlled unit that was given beefed-up internals to handle even more boost than the engineers were dialing in.  Ford liked to tout that this turbo motor was just like a V8, and there were not far off considering this Mustang made as much horsepower as it stablemate 5.0 GT.  But what made the difference of the SVO was that it had a true European flair on the road.  That comes from features like the four-wheel disc brakes, Koni shocks, McPherson strut front suspension, and quad shock rear end.  Plus there were other great driving features such as the Borg Warner five-speed manual transmission, versatile 3.73 rear gears, and power assisted rack & pinion steering,

Complete with original title documentation, this 2nd-owner (who just rescued it out of the original owners garage) SVO remains a lot of fun, and the price for this low batch collectible can't be beat.  Call today!!
title: 1986 Ford Mustang SVO Turbo

description: For sale in our Atlanta showroom is a classic 1966 Ford Mustang. This A-code pony is a beauty and ready to cruise on down to the drive-in or next show! Powering this 66 Ford Mustang for sale is a straight six.  This Ford engine has plenty of pep in its step, with a snappy throttle, and a subtle exhaust from its factory style exhaust. Backing the reliable six is a 3-speed automatic transmission. Add in disc brakes, and power steering, and you have yourself one fun and easy driving Mustang for sale. The power is thrown to the pavement with ease.  At a glance, it's easy to see that this Mustang is vintage in pedigree. This pretty pony is adorned with a beautiful blue paint. This driver quality stallion has a nostalgic look that's a real blast from the past! With just the right amount of chrome and polished goodies, you can see how the 60s transformed from big bumpers and tail fins, to sharp lines and pure presence. The interior is no different, with a deluxe pony vinyl interior. The sporty buckets up front straddle the shifter and console nicely, while the bench out back begs you to have some friends tag along. Everyone understands why the Mustang was such a popular seller and the car to beat. Options on this 1966 Ford Mustang coupe for sale, include: A/C, AM radio, power brakes, power steering, seat belts, vinyl interior, and radial tires. Whether you're looking for a cruiser, a grocery get'r, or you're simply a Ford enthusiast who love originality, this '66 Mustang for sale is for you! The V8 power plant is paired to an SelectShift Cruise-o-Matic automatic transmission that does an amazing job of planting power to pavement. This iconic pony car is sporting a coat of Mustang red paint with a two-tone hood with functional air scoops to help this pony breathe.
